25/05/2005
ROME, Italy -- Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski visited Rome on Tuesday (24 May) to discuss bilateral ties with Italian Defence Minister Antonio Martino and Foreign Minister Gianfranco Fini.
They also talked about issues related to Skopje's Euro-Atlantic integration bids.
Martino reportedly told Buckovski that Macedonia is on the right track regarding its efforts to join NATO.
He also praised the country's contribution to the international coalitions in Afghanistan and Iraq.
(Macedonian Government Web site - 25/05/05;
Telma TV - 24/05/05)
